  "campus": "Atlanta",
  "campus_description": "ATL@ATLANTA",
  "course_description": "This class provides an overview of the foundational principles of state and local taxation in the United States. The course does not concentrate on the laws of any particular state nor is any prior course in taxation required. The course focuses on the economic, administrative, political, and constitutional and federal law constraints on states' and localities' authority to impose taxes, including limits arising under the U.S. Constitution and principles of federal preemption. The course also examines how state and local governments balance revenue needs with the goal of attracting jobs and investment in developing sound tax policy. Instruction is grounded in case studies, many drawn from the Professors' experience representing some of the world's largest companies. Subject to performance and availability, select students may have the opportunity to apply for an internship at Eversheds Sutherland (US) LLP.",
  "course_notes": "Final Assessment: Self-Scheduled Exam",
